    "costs": "500",
    "actions_taken": [
      "BSEE conducted on-site incident follow-up investigation on July 14, 2021",
      "Collected all available documents including JSAs, pictures, and lift plan",
      "Identified incorrect crane slings as root cause"
    ],
    "summary": "On July 10, 2021, at approximately 18:15 hours, during sidetrack operations on the A005 well at MC Block 773, a dropped object incident occurred when a stinger hook struck a walkway handrail while lifting a crossover sub using 35-foot slings. The broken handrail (5.5 ft by 1.5 in square tubing, 13.6 lbs) fell approximately 75 feet to the deck below. No injuries occurred, though one person was 6 feet from the impact location. Root cause was determined to be use of incorrect (too long) crane slings and lack of communication between driller and crane operator.",
    "recommendations": [],
